If we considered hypothetical adaptation to the 95th percentile temperature, the increases are much lower than those without accounting for adaptation (
 
  Fig 3
  and Table D in 
 
  S1 Appendix
 ). For the high-variant population scenario, the heatwave-related excess mortality is expected to increase in all the countries/regions except Moldova and Japan, under all scenarios of greenhouse gas emissions. For the low-variant population scenario, heatwave-related excess mortality is expected to decrease in Italy, Japan, Moldova, and Spain, under all the scenarios of greenhouse gas emissions. The decreases in heatwave-related excess mortality in Japan and Moldova are mainly driven by population decrease in the future (
 
  Table 2
 ). The results for each community are similar to the country/region level results (Fig M-X in 
 
  S1 Appendix
 ).
